keycloak-remember-me-authenticator (vendored)
=============================================

This directory contains a vendored copy of the keycloak-remember-me-authenticator
SPI plugin by Stefan Over ("Herdo").

  Upstream:   https://github.com/Herdo/keycloak-remember-me-authenticator
  Commit:     de35b3603de348c44a532c011079d3e687ab10b6
  License:    MIT (see ./LICENSE)
  Copyright:  (c) 2023 Stefan Over

Why vendored
------------
The upstream repo's prebuilt 1.0.0 JAR release (2023) is compiled against
Keycloak 20.x and ships with a pom.xml that pins stale dependency versions
(see upstream issue #9). Rather than consuming the published JAR, we rebuild
from source against the Keycloak release this image targets (controlled by
the `KC_VERSION` build arg) so the plugin's classpath is binary-compatible
with the running server.

Local modifications vs upstream
-------------------------------
Java source under src/main/java:
    VERBATIM. No changes (including license headers and code style).

SPI registration src/main/resources/META-INF/services/org.keycloak.authentication.AuthenticatorFactory:
    VERBATIM.

pom.xml:
    REWRITTEN against the Keycloak 26.5.7 parent BOM. Specifically:
      - Imports org.keycloak:keycloak-parent:26.5.7 via <dependencyManagement>
        (per Keycloak 26.5 server-development docs).
      - Drops the upstream keycloak-services dependency: not referenced by
        any import in the Java sources.
      - Drops the upstream <distributionManagement> block: we don't publish
        to GitHub Packages from this repo, the JAR is consumed only by the
        sibling Dockerfile.
      - Targets Java 21 release (maven.compiler.release=21) — Keycloak 26
        supports JDK 17 and 21; we standardize on 21 to track the latest
        Keycloak-supported LTS.
      - Bumps maven-compiler-plugin to 3.13.0.
      - Sets <finalName>keycloak-remember-me-authenticator</finalName> for
        a predictable JAR filename consumed by the Dockerfile.

src/main/resources/META-INF/jboss-deployment-structure.xml:
    OMITTED. That file is for the legacy WildFly-based Keycloak deployment
    model (pre-17). Keycloak 17+ is Quarkus-based and uses the
    /opt/keycloak/providers/ JAR drop + `kc.sh build` model, which makes the
    JBoss module descriptor a no-op. Excluding it keeps the artifact clean.
